Subject: Re:Horn won't beep - signal lights won't cancel

John, the gap between your switch cluster and the steering wheel is too 
great.  You must loosen the (no doubt non-factory, standard hex-head M8 
bolt) and adjust the gap until the cancelling device works and the horn ring 
connects.  Then go buy the break-away/shearing bolt to replace the no doubt 
non-factory bolt currently holding it up so that you won't impale yourself 
in a front end collision you are fortunate enough to survive.

Joe
1978 Westy Deluxe
formerly had a 1977 Westy Standard with a wandering switch...


